<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<package xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/packaging/2010/07/nuspec.xsd">
  <metadata>
    <id>aithershell</id>
    <title>AitherShell</title>
    <version>1.0.0</version>
    <authors>Aitherium</authors>
    <owners>Aitherium</owners>
    <summary>AitherShell - Run AI agents from your terminal</summary>
    <description>
AitherShell is a closed-source commercial CLI for running AI agents from your terminal.

Features:
- Interactive REPL with command history
- Multiple output formats (text, JSON, private)
- 12 AI personas with unique perspectives
- License-based pricing (free/pro/enterprise)
- No external dependencies

Quick Start:
1. Set your license key: setx AITHERIUM_LICENSE_KEY "your-key"
2. Run: aither --help
3. Get a license: https://aitherium.com/free

Support: support@aitherium.com
Docs: https://docs.aitherium.com/aithershell
    </description>
    <projectUrl>https://aitherium.com/aithershell</projectUrl>
    <projectSourceUrl>https://github.com/Aitherium/aithershell</projectSourceUrl>
    <bugTrackerUrl>https://github.com/Aitherium/aithershell/issues</bugTrackerUrl>
    <licenseUrl>https://github.com/Aitherium/aithershell/blob/main/LICENSE</licenseUrl>
    <requireLicenseAcceptance>true</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <iconUrl>https://aitherium.com/images/aithershell-icon.png</iconUrl>
    <releaseNotes>
## AitherShell v1.0.0 - Production Release

✅ Compiled Windows binary (86 MB aither.exe)
✅ License key validation (free/pro/enterprise tiers)
✅ Interactive REPL with command history
✅ Multiple output formats (text, JSON, private)
✅ 12 AI personas support
✅ Safety levels (paranoid, strict, professional, relaxed)
✅ Effort-based model routing (1-10)

See https://github.com/Aitherium/aithershell/releases/v1.0.0 for full details.
    </releaseNotes>
    <tags>ai agents cli terminal aitheros</tags>
